cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.SE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it discusses Content-Centric Networking (CCN) as an alternative to IP-based Internet Architecture. It also focuses on the design and implementation of KRB-CCN, a complete authorization and access control system for private CCNs. 

It could also belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it discusses security services such as content authenticity, integrity, confidentiality, authorization, and access control. 

Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses in-network content caching and better network utilization. 

Systems and Control (cs.SY) could also be a likely sub-category as the paper describes the design and implementation of a system for authorization and access control. 

Finally, Software Engineering (cs.SE) could be a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the design and implementation of KRB-CCN.
